COMMENTS: The unique Delacour and Jabouille field number of the holotype was given in the original description. The authors listed 20 specimens in their type series. Of the 19 paratypes , eight came to AMNH : AMNH 290954–290957 , three males and one female from Cha Pa
;
AMNH 290958 and 290959, a male and a female from Loquiho
;
and AMNH 290960 and 290961, one male and one unsexed from Fan­si­pan
.

The initials ‘‘R.P.’’ used by Hartert for Soulié refer to ‘‘Reverendissimus Pater’’ (5 most holy father), an honorific apparently given this missionary martyr (
Fournier, 1932: 115–120
).
